{"search_data": "ManipurSAUBHAGYA Scheme launched in Manipur to Provide Electricity 1.75 lakh HouseholdsMoreover, the central government has assured that they will provide expected financial assistance for procuring of transformers, meters etc. to strengthen the power sector in Manipur. This scheme is being implemented by the Rural Electrification Corporation Limited (REC), Under the Ministry of Power. The beneficiary of the scheme will be identified using Socio Economic and Caste Census (SECC), 2011 data.Recently, the central government launched Saubhagya portal to check the working progress of electrification of households in the country. The citizen can make their registration on the portal to pay the electricity bills and get the information regarding reducing power losses.On the Saubhagya portal, the candidate will get the relevant information regarding electrification areas-wise. The government will provide electrical connections to the 4 crore un-electrified households by 2018 Under Saubhagya scheme.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}